                "id": "CVE-2015-7972", 
                "modified": "2015-11-02T11:19:10.610-05:00", 
                "summary": "The (1) libxl_set_memory_target function in tools/libxl/libxl.c and (2) libxl__build_post function in tools/libxl/libxl_dom.c in Xen 3.4.x through 4.6.x do not properly calculate the balloon size when using the populate-on-demand (PoD) system, which allows local HVM guest users to cause a denial of service (guest crash) via unspecified vectors related to \"heavy memory pressure.\""
            }
